  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Tim Berners-Lee
Lived:         1955 - present
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     World Wide Web
Contribution:  Invented the Web in 1989; gave it to the world for free
Quote:         "The web does not just connect machines, it connects people."

Name:          Charles Darwin
Lived:         1809 - 1882
Nationality:   English
Field:         Biology
Known For:     Evolution by Natural Selection
Contribution:  On the Origin of Species; explained diversity of life on Earth
Quote:         "It is not the strongest that survives, but the most adaptable."

Name:          Ada Lovelace
Lived:         1815 - 1852
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     First computer algorithm
Contribution:  Wrote first algorithm for Babbage's machine; recognized computing potential
Quote:         "The Analytical Engine weaves algebraic patterns."

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

Concept:    GDP
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Total value of all goods and services produced in a country annually
Formula:    GDP = C + I + G + (X-M)
Economist:  Simon Kuznets
Example:    USA GDP 2023: $27.4 trillion; China: $17.9 trillion

Concept:    Central Bank
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government institution managing currency, money supply, interest rates
Formula:    Taylor Rule for interest rates
Economist:  John Taylor
Example:    US Federal Reserve raised rates to 5.25% in 2023 to fight inflation

